description.narrative: Critical region-wide research on social services workforce strengthening, parenting support to reduce violence, child online protection and VAC-VAW intersections was completed and partnerships were expanded beyond traditional child protection actors, especially in the fields of child online protection, children affected by migration and children with disabilities. Two groundbreaking declarations were adopted by ASEAN Heads of State on children affected by migration and on child online protection, and ASEAN Member States recommitted to advancing children's rights as part of the CRC@30 commemoration. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/08/2020
